The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Revelation by Deco
                                                                                                                                                                                           In and out
                      
	Revelation by Deco   
	New Chelsea recruit Deco has revealed he turned down lucrative offers from America and Saudi Arabia to move to Stamford Bridge. Deco claims a number of MLS sides and Saudi Arabian clubs were keen on signing him, but that he opted to sign for Chelsea .  
	Fabiano deal         
	 Luis Fabiano has signed a contract extension with Sevilla to put an end to speculation about his future. The Brazilian-born striker has committed his future to the club until June 2011. The new contract includes a termination clause of 19.8million and an undisclosed raise.         
	Firm offer         
	 Real Madrid forward Robinho could be headed to Chelsea after his agent revealed the club have proposed a firm offer.         
	Desperate Juventus         
	 Juventus are ready to launch a 15m bid for Arsenals Robin van Persie, who they see as an ideal replacement for Pavel Nedved.         
	Transfer in doubt         
	 Gareth Barrys proposed move to Liverpool is in doubt as the deal hinges on Xabi Alonso leaving the club, but the Spaniard wants to remain at Anfield.         
	Costly bidding         
	 Portsmouth manager Harry Redknapp has said he is looking at offloading five or six players to finance a bid for Chelsea winger Shaun Wright-Phillips.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
